Hi CD,
I have read both Vivid Hosting and WPI Docs, and both recommend against using the new radio in a single-radio setup. I understand this is because it is limited to 2.4 GHz, which is prone to interference from nearby Wi-Fi signals. However, our workshop lack both cellular and Wi-Fi coverage. In this situation, can we use the new radio, or would it be better to continue using the old one?

Your milage may vary.

Although band congestion is a major factor, one you missed is heat.

The new radio prioritizes 6GHz. During extended use like at a scrimmage, or during a practice where the robot is on for long or repeated periods without appreciable cooldown time, the radio becomes quite warm.

Down at the chip level it’s more like “hot”, and because of the radio priority the 2.4GHz radio has its performance cut in favor of processor performance, and 6GHz performance.

So teams that were operating fine for 10min are suddenly confused as they experience range reduction, disconnects, etc…

Thank you. I saw the general warnings that radio gets hot but Vivid documentation doesn’t mention any additional heat produced under 2.4Ghz Access Point section so I only thought of Wi-Fi congestion. In that case, I guess old radio is a better option.
